{\cf1\f1\fs22 18}When Jesus had said this, he went out with his disciples and crossed the Kidron ravine to a place where there was a garden, into which he and his disciples went.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}The place was well known to Judas, the betrayer, for Jesus and his disciples had often met there.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}So Judas, who had obtained the soldiers of the Roman garrison, and some guards from the chief priests and the Pharisees, came there with lanterns, torches, and weapons.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Jesus, aware of all that was coming upon him, went to meet them, and said to them, \uc1\u8216*For whom are you looking?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}\uc1\u8216*Jesus of Nazareth,\uc1\u8217* was their answer. \uc1\u8216*I am he,\uc1\u8217* said Jesus. (Judas, the betrayer, was also standing with them.){\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}When Jesus said \uc1\u8220*I am he,\uc1\u8221* they drew back and fell to the ground.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}So he again asked for whom they were looking, and they answered, \uc1\u8216*Jesus of Nazareth.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}\uc1\u8216*I have already told you that I am he,\uc1\u8217* replied Jesus, \uc1\u8216*so, if it is for me that you are looking, let these people go.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}This was in fulfilment of his words \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Of those whom you have given me I have not lost one.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}At this, Simon Peter, who had a sword with him, drew it, and struck the high priest\uc1\u8217*s servant, and cut off his right ear. The servant\uc1\u8217*s name was Malchus.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}But Jesus said to Peter, \uc1\u8216*Sheathe your sword. Should I not drink the cup which the Father has given me?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}So the soldiers of the garrison, with their commanding officer and the Jewish guards, arrested Jesus and bound him,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}and took him first of all to Annas. Annas was the father-in-law of Caiaphas, who was high priest that year.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}It was Caiaphas who had counselled the religious authorities, that it was best that one person should die for the people.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Meanwhile Simon Peter followed Jesus, and so did another disciple. That disciple, being well-known to the high priest, went with Jesus into the high priest\uc1\u8217*s courtyard,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}while Peter stood outside by the door. Presently the other disciple \uc1\u8211* the one well-known to the high priest \uc1\u8211* went out and spoke to the portress, and brought Peter in.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}So the maidservant said to Peter, \uc1\u8216*Aren\uc1\u8217*t you also one of this man\uc1\u8217*s disciples?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
 \uc1\u8216*No, I am not,\uc1\u8217* he said.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}The servants and guards were standing round a charcoal fire (which they had made because it was cold), and were warming themselves. Peter, too, was with them, standing and warming himself.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}The high priest questioned Jesus about his disciples and about his teaching.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}\uc1\u8216*For my part,\uc1\u8217* answered Jesus, \uc1\u8216*I have spoken to all the world openly. I always taught in some synagogue, or in the Temple Courts, places where everyone assembles, and I never spoke of anything in secret.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Why question me? Question those who have listened to me as to what I have spoken about to them. They must know what I said.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}When Jesus said this, one of the guards, who was standing near, gave him a blow with his hand. \uc1\u8216*Do you answer the high priest like that?\uc1\u8217* he exclaimed.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}\uc1\u8216*If I said anything wrong, give evidence about it,\uc1\u8217* replied Jesus, \uc1\u8216*but if not, why do you strike me?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}Annas sent him bound to Caiaphas the high priest.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Meanwhile Simon Peter was standing there, warming himself; so they said to him, \uc1\u8216*Aren\uc1\u8217*t you also one of his disciples?\uc1\u8217* Peter denied it. \uc1\u8216*No, I am not,\uc1\u8217* he said.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}One of the high priest\uc1\u8217*s servants, a relation of the man whose ear Peter had cut off, exclaimed, \uc1\u8216*Didn\uc1\u8217*t I myself see you with him in the garden?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}Peter again denied it; and at that moment a cock crowed.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}From Caiaphas they took Jesus to the Government house. It was early in the morning. But they did not enter the Government house themselves, otherwise they might become defiled, and so be unable to eat the Passover.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}Therefore Pilate came outside to speak to them. \uc1\u8216*What charge do you bring against this man?\uc1\u8217* he asked.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}\uc1\u8216*If he had not been a criminal, we should not have given him up to you,\uc1\u8217* they answered.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}\uc1\u8216*Take him yourselves,\uc1\u8217* said Pilate, \uc1\u8216*and try him by your own Law.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
 \uc1\u8216*We have no power to put anyone to death,\uc1\u8217* the authorities replied \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}in fulfilment of what Jesus had said when indicating the death that he was destined to die.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}After that, Pilate went into the Government house again, and calling Jesus up, asked him, \uc1\u8216*Are you the king of the Jews?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}\uc1\u8216*Do you ask me that yourself?\uc1\u8217* replied Jesus, \uc1\u8216*or did others say it to you about me?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}\uc1\u8216*Do you take me for a Jew?\uc1\u8217* was Pilate\uc1\u8217*s answer. \uc1\u8216*It is your own nation and the chief priests who have given you up to me. What have you done?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}\uc1\u8216*My kingly power,\uc1\u8217* replied Jesus, \uc1\u8216*is not due to this world. If it had been so, my servants would be doing their utmost to prevent my being given up to the authorities; but my kingly power is not from the world.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}\uc1\u8216*So you are a king after all!\uc1\u8217* exclaimed Pilate. \uc1\u8216*Yes, it is true I am a king,\uc1\u8217* answered Jesus. \uc1\u8216*I was born for this, I have come into the world for this \uc1\u8211* to bear testimony to the truth. Everyone who is on the side of truth listens to my voice.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}\uc1\u8216*What is truth?\uc1\u8217* exclaimed Pilate. After saying this, he went out to the crowd again, and said, \uc1\u8216*For my part, I find nothing with which he can be charged.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 39}It is, however, the custom for me to grant you the release of one man at the Passover Festival. Do you wish for the release of the king of the Jews?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}\uc1\u8216*No, not this man,\uc1\u8217* they shouted again, \uc1\u8216*but Barabbas!\uc1\u8217* This Barabbas was a robber.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 19}After that, Pilate had Jesus scourged.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}The soldiers made a crown with some thorns and put it on his head and threw a purple robe round him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}They kept coming up to him and saying, \uc1\u8216*Long live the king of the Jews!\uc1\u8217* and they gave him blow after blow with their hands.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Pilate again came outside, and said to the people, \uc1\u8216*Look! I am bringing him out to you, so that you may know that I find nothing with which he can be charged.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Then Jesus came outside, wearing the crown of thorns and the purple robe; and Pilate said to them, \uc1\u8216*Here is the man!\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}When the chief priests and the guards saw him, they shouted, \uc1\u8216*Crucify him! Crucify him!\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
 \uc1\u8216*Take him yourselves and crucify him,\uc1\u8217* said Pilate. \uc1\u8216*For my part, I find nothing with which he can be charged.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}\uc1\u8216*But we,\uc1\u8217* replied the crowd, \uc1\u8216*have a Law, under which he deserves death for making himself out to be the Son of God.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}When Pilate heard what they said, he became still more alarmed;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}and, going into the Government house again, he said to Jesus, \uc1\u8216*Where do you come from?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}But Jesus made no reply. So Pilate said to him, \uc1\u8216*Do you refuse to speak to me? Don\uc1\u8217*t you know that I have power to release you, and have power to crucify you?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}\uc1\u8216*You would have no power over me at all,\uc1\u8217* answered Jesus, \uc1\u8216*if it had not been given you from above; and, therefore, the man who betrayed me to you is guilty of the greater sin.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}This made Pilate anxious to release him; but the crowd shouted, \uc1\u8216*If you release that man, you are no friend of the Emperor! Anyone who makes himself out to be a king is setting himself against the Emperor!\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}On hearing what they said, Pilate brought Jesus out, and took his seat on the Bench at a place called \uc1\u8220*The Stone Pavement\uc1\u8221* \uc1\u8211* in Hebrew \uc1\u8220*Gabbatha.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}It was the Passover Preparation day, and about noon. Then he said to the crowd, \uc1\u8216*Here is your king!\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}At that the people shouted, \uc1\u8216*Kill him! Kill him! Crucify him!\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
 \uc1\u8216*What! Should I crucify your king?\uc1\u8217* exclaimed Pilate. \uc1\u8216*We have no king but the Emperor,\uc1\u8217* replied the chief priests;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}so Pilate gave Jesus up to them to be crucified.
\par}

