{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 20}On the first day of the week, early in the morning, while it was still dark, Mary of Magdala went to the tomb, and saw that the stone had been removed.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}So she came running to Simon Peter, and to that other disciple who was Jesus\uc1\u8217* friend, and said to them, \uc1\u8216*They have taken away the Master out of the tomb, and we do not know where they have laid him!\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}So, Peter started off with that other disciple, and they went to the tomb.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}The two began running together; but the other disciple ran faster than Peter, and reached the tomb first.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Stooping down, he saw the linen wrappings lying there, but did not go in.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Presently Simon Peter came following behind him, and went into the tomb; and he looked at the linen wrappings lying there,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}and the cloth which had been on Jesus\uc1\u8217* head, not lying with the wrappings, but rolled up on one side, separately.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Then the other disciple, who had reached the tomb first, went inside too, and he saw for himself and was convinced.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}For they did not then understand the passage of scripture which says that Jesus must rise again from the dead.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}The disciples then returned to their companions.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Meanwhile Mary was standing close outside the tomb, weeping. Still weeping, she leant forward into the tomb,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}and perceived two angels clothed in white sitting there, where the body of Jesus had been lying, one where the head and the other where the feet had been.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}\uc1\u8216*Why are you weeping?\uc1\u8217* asked the angels. \uc1\u8216*They have taken my Master away,\uc1\u8217* she answered, \uc1\u8216*and I do not know where they have laid him.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}After saying this, she turned round, and looked at Jesus standing there, but she did not know that it was Jesus.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}\uc1\u8216*Why are you weeping? Whom are you seeking?\uc1\u8217* he asked. Supposing him to be the gardener, Mary answered, \uc1\u8216*If it was you, Sir, who carried him away, tell me where you have laid him, and I will take him away myself.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}\uc1\u8216*Mary!\uc1\u8217* said Jesus. She turned round, and exclaimed in Hebrew, \uc1\u8216*Rabboni!\uc1\u8217* (or, as we should say, \uc1\u8220*teacher\uc1\u8221*).{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}\uc1\u8216*Do not hold me,\uc1\u8217* Jesus said, \uc1\u8216*for I have not yet ascended to the Father. But go to my brothers, and tell them that I am ascending to him who is my Father and their Father, my God and their God.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Mary of Magdala went and told the disciples that she had seen the Master, and that he had said this to her.
