 \uc1\u8216*No,\uc1\u8217* they answered.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}\uc1\u8216*Cast your net to the right of the boat,\uc1\u8217* he said, \uc1\u8216*and you will find fish.\uc1\u8217* So they cast the net, and now they could not haul it in because of the quantity of fish.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}The disciple whom Jesus loved said to Peter, \uc1\u8216*It is the Master!\uc1\u8217* When Simon Peter heard that it was the Master, he fastened his coat round him (for he had taken it off), and threw himself into the sea.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}But the rest of the disciples came in the boat (for they were only about a hundred yards from shore), dragging the net full of fish.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}When they had come ashore, they found a charcoal fire ready, with some fish already on it, and some bread as well.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}\uc1\u8216*Bring some of the fish which you have just caught,\uc1\u8217* said Jesus.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}So Simon Peter got into the boat and hauled the net ashore full of large fish, a hundred and fifty-three of them; and yet, although there were so many, the net had not been torn.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}\uc1\u8216*Come and have breakfast.\uc1\u8217*, Jesus said. None of the disciples dared ask him who he was, because they knew it was the Master.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Jesus went and took the bread and gave it to them, and the fish too.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}This was the third time that Jesus showed himself to the disciples after he had risen from the dead.
